WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Hey, and welcome to Edch Hustle.
I want to

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:04.000
show you this workflow
that I think

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:05.000
might be helpful for you.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.000
So let me tell you this situation
that I'm at right now.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Let's say that you have
a video on

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.000
YouTube and you want
to generate a

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
transcript, so what you're probably

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.000
thinking of doing is just
taking that

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
link, copying the link,
going to ChatGPT,

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.000
and saying, "Hey, can you create
a transcript

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
for this video?" and then
pasting that

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.000
link, but this is the response
that I

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
just got from ChatGPT.
It's unable to

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
provide a transcript due to
copyright

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.000
constraints. It goes through to

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
kind of give an overview,
but all this is,

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
is summarizing the information
that's in

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
the video's description.
Then at the end,

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
as you can see, it says,
"Hey, I recommend

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.000
watching the video directly."
Well, that's

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.000
what I'm trying to avoid doing.
So I'm

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:46.000
going to show you how you can use
ChatGPT

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:49.000
and YouTube to create
an awesome-looking

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:52.000
transcript of any video.
Now, what

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.000
you might not know is that there
is a

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.000
YouTube transcript in every video.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:00:58.000
You just have to be able
to find it,

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
and it is hidden. So what you'll
have to do is

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
go to the video, go to where the

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.000
description is, and click More.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
And now, if you scroll down
to the bottom,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.000
you can see a button that says
Show transcript.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.000
When I click Show transcript,
I can see

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.000
this whole transcript
right over here to

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.000
the right. So here's what
I need to do.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:19.000
I just need to take all of that text,

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:20.000
highlight it, and select it all,

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.000
and then I'm going to do
Control+C.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:26.000
I'm going to copy that text.
Now I'm

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.000
going to go back to ChatGPT,
and I'm

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:30.000
going to ask it to create
a clean

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
transcript, and I will paste
that text.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.000
Now look at this. I'm unable
to submit

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.000
this because I believe
the transcript

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:41.000
from the video I'm trying to do
exceeds

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.000
the character count.
You can see what it

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.000
says right over here:
The message is too

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:47.000
long. I'm stuck, right? Nope.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Here's what you'll do.
We'll take the YouTube

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:52.000
transcript text, which is still
copied to

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:53.000
our clipboard,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.000
and I'm going to paste it
right here in a Google Doc.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Now, it doesn't have to be
a Google Doc.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
It can be whatever
word processing format

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:01.000
of your choice. You just want
to make sure

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:04.000
that you can export or save this
as a

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.000
file type, probably a PDF
or a Microsoft

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:10.000
Word document. So from here,
I'm just

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.000
going to go to File,
I'm going to choose

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
Download, and I will choose a PDF.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.000
So everything is the same.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:20.000
I'm just going to say,
"Can you create a clean transcript?"

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:21.000
And this time,
I'm going to click on the

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.000
plus button, and I'm going
to upload that

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.000
PDF directly into ChatGPT.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
All right, now that has been uploaded.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Let me go ahead and submit this,
and take a look at this.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
ChatGPT went in and it gave me
a much

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.000
cleaner transcript. There's no
timestamps

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
or any other things that I don't need

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.000
in this particular document.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
Everything is capitalized,
the grammar is correct,

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:50.000
and this looks awesome.

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:53.000
Now from here, I'm just going
to go to Copy.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:55.000
I'm going to copy all of this text.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
I'm going to go back to my Google Doc,

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.000
I'll paste the text, and then
check this out.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:03.000
I have a really nice transcript

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:06.000
that I can use for whatever purpose
that I want.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:09.000
Now, what I like about adding this
into ChatGPT

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.000
is that at any time,
I can open this thread

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.000
and come back to this particular discussion.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.000
So now I can ask it
a follow-up question.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.000
All right, I'm going to say,

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:23.000
"Can you summarize this in three paragraphs?"

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.000
And right there are my three paragraphs.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.000
ChatGPT has summarized
the key points.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.000
So again, if you have
a super long video,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:34.000
this might be one way
to kind of get

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:36.000
just an overview
of what it's about.

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.000
So that's it. I hope that,
I hope that

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.000
this has been helpful for you.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:43.000
Again, you can create
a transcript this way.

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:47.000
Again, you can create a... again,
so that's it.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:49.000
I hope this video
has been helpful.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
You can create a clean transcript

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:54.000
from YouTube using ChatGPT,
so thank you so

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:56.000
much for watching this video.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:58.000
If this is something that has been helpful,

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:02.000
please like, comment, and subscribe,

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:05.000
and, as always, have a great day.
